


To install the GIMP plugin, copy everything in the "gimp-plugin"-folder to GIMP's "plug-ins"-folder, e. g. in Linux:
      cp -R gimp-plugin/* ~/.gimp-2.6/plug-ins
or on a Mac: 
      cp -R gimp-plugin/* ~/Library/Application\ Support/Gimp/plug-ins/
and make the .py-files executable if they aren't.
Don't try to copy the gimp-plugin folder directly - it doesn't work.

This folder includes a modified version of SimpleOSC from
      http://www.ixi-audio.net/content/body_backyard_python.html
(in gimp-plugin/osc).

Put the GimpOSC-folder (containing the SuperCollider classes GimpOSC & Bitmap) in your SuperCollider/Extensions folder. In Linux e. g.
      cp -R GimpOSC ~/share/SuperCollider/Extensions
or an a Mac:
      cp -R GimpOSC ~/Library/Application\ Support/SuperCollider/Extensions
   